1 19–1408.
2 (a) (1) Subject to subsection (c) of this section, the Department shall make a
3 site visit and conduct a full survey of each licensed nursing home at least once per calendar
4 year.
5 (2) Unless otherwise required by federal law, all surveys shall be
6 unannounced.
7 (b) (1) Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Department shall
8 initiate an investigation of a nursing home complaint alleging actual harm within 10
9 business days after receiving the complaint.
10 (2) If the Department receives a complaint against a nursing home alleging
11 immediate jeopardy to a resident, the Department:
12 (i) Shall make every effort to investigate the complaint within 24
13 hours after receiving the complaint; and
14 (ii) Shall investigate the complaint not later than 48 hours after
15 receiving the complaint.
16 (c) If ownership of a licensed nursing home is transferred to a person that does
17 not own or operate another nursing home in the State at the time of the transfer, the
18 Department shall conduct:
19 (1) The first full survey of the licensed nursing home as required under
20 subsection (a) of this section within 3 months after the date of transfer; and
21 (2) An unannounced, on–site follow–up survey of the licensed nursing
22 home that covers any deficiencies noted in the full survey within 120 days after the full
23 survey was completed.
24 (D) (1) ON REQUEST OF A COUNTY, THE SECRETARY SHALL DELEGATE TO
25 THE COUNTY THE AUTHORITY TO CONDUCT SITE VISITS AND FULL SURVEYS OF
26 NURSING HOMES UNDER THIS SECTION.
27 (2) THE DEPARTMENT AND THE COUNTY SHALL EQUALLY SHARE THE
28 COSTS OF CONDUCTING SITE VISITS AND FULL SURVEYS DELEGATED BY THE
29 SECRETARY UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
30 (D) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (3) OF THIS SUBSECTION, IF BY JULY 1,
31 2026, THE DEPARTMENT IS 6 MONTHS OR MORE BEHIND THE FEDERAL
32 REQUIREMENT OF CONDUCTING NURSING HOME SURVEYS EVERY 15.9 MONTHS
33 ACCORDING TO THE DEPARTMENT’S MOST RECENT DATA, ON REQUEST OF A

