1 COUNTY, THE SECRETARY SHALL DELEGATE TO THE COUNTY THE AUTHORITY TO
2 AUGMENT STATE NURSING HOME SURVEY STAFF USING COUNTY FUNDS IN
3 ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SUBSECTION.
4 (2) WITHIN 45 DAYS AFTER A COUNTY MAKES A REQUEST UNDER
5 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
6 (I) INITIATE A MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING WITH THE
7 COUNTY TO USE COUNTY FUNDS TO CONDUCT SURVEYS AND COMPLAINT
8 INVESTIGATIONS OF NURSING HOMES; AND
9 (II) DEVELOP A PLAN WITH THE COUNTY ON HOW TO
10 IMPLEMENT THE AUGMENTATION OF STAFF.
11 (3) A MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING INITIATED OR A PLAN OF
12 ACTION DEVELOPED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION MAY NOT RESTRICT A COUNTY’S
13 PROGRESSION TO THE NEXT SURVEY TIER IF AN EXEMPTION FROM THE TIERS IS
14 AUTHORIZED BY THE CENTERS FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID SERVICES FOR
15 NURSING HOMES.
16 (4) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL INCLUDE, AS PART OF THE REPORTING
17 REQUIREMENTS UNDER § 19–308(B)(4) OF THIS TITLE AND § 19–1409(E) OF THIS
18 SUBTITLE:
19 (I) EACH MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING INITIATED
20 UNDER THIS SUBSECTION; AND
21 (II) THE NUMBER OF SURVEYS COMPLETED UNDER THE
22 MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING INITIATED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION.
23 (E) BEGINNING JULY 1, 2025, AND EVERY 6 MONTHS THEREAFTER, THE
24 DEPARTMENT SHALL REPORT TO EACH AREA AGENCY ON AGING:
25 (1) THE NAMES OF EACH NURSING HOME SURVEYED BY THE STATE
26 AND THE DATES OF EACH STATE SURVEY COMPLETED IN THE COUNTY DURING THE
27 IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING 6 MONTHS; AND
28 (2) THE AVERAGE STATEWIDE INTERVAL IN MONTHS BETWEEN
29 REQUIRED RECERTIFICATION SURVEYS AS COMPARED WITH THE FEDERAL
30 REQUIREMENT OF 15.9 MONTHS.
31 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
32 October June 1, 2025.

